Quote:  Down there, webs of standing water transect a rippling carpet of red tussock, <i>Chionochloa rubra</i>... red tussock thrives on waterlogged or frosty flats... [29] In the wetter areas, such as Southland, red tussock raced across the low-lying hills. <i>Ibid.</i> 35 Red tussock, <i>Chionochloa rubra</i>.. grows to a metre high and is one of the most widely distributed tall tussocks, occurring from the volcanic plateau of the central North Island, through most of the South Island and into Stewart Island.
